div.p:
The most remarkable seats of noblemen and others are Audley-End, Lord Braybrooks;
                    Thorndon, Lord Petre; Wanstead, now dilapidated, Hon. William Wellesley Pole;
                    Easton Lodge, Lord Maynard; Felix Hall, Lord Western; Mistley Hall, C. Manners
                    Sutton; Dagenham Park, Sir Thomas Neave; the Hyde, Theo. Disney, Esq.;
                    Chig-well, Sir Eliab Harvey; Hill Hall, Sir William Smyth; Cranham Hall, Lady
                    Davy; Weald Hall, Christopher Tower, Esq.; Boreham House, Sir John Tyrell; Coped
                    Hall, Mr Conyers; Mark Hall, Mr Arkwright; Stansted Hall, Mr Fuller Maitland;
                    and many others.
